My cousin Mark Thomas Carter (1980-2007), SOC- better known as Badger to his teammates, was born and raised in Fallbrook, CA. He stayed and worked for a summer on our ranch in Wyoming when we were both 12, that season together hunting and working ignited his heroic imagination. From that time on Mark knew his God-given mission in life was to become a Navy SEAL and I watched the years tick on as he never wavered from what his soul required of him.
Not a day goes by that I don’t think of my cousin Mark, how he raised the bar for himself at a young age, rose to the occasion, and became an unforgettable force to everyone in his wake. Grief, I’ve learned, is really just love with no place to go, all the love you want to give but cannot. This Memorial Day let us honor all who have fallen and all who have served and are still bearing this great burden of grief.
Heroes are most effective not alone but in a network. I have come to know some of the men who have shed blood, sweat and tears next to my cousin…these men are the unsung, quiet heroes of our nation who have been divinely sanctioned to protect and serve.

#navyseals #frogman #patriot #honor #memorialday  #America
